3. Nodes & Deployment

Node	Hardware	Software	Role

Home	Laptop/RPi	AQARIONZ Core	Daily life signals, meditation, baseline testing
Cave	Sensors: IMU, CO₂, barometer	Core + Cave Module	Darkness baseline, boundary experiments
River	Sensors: flow, temp, sound	Core + River Module	Environmental patterns and story sync
Storm Porch	Sensors: wind, pressure, EM	Core + Storm Module	Extreme state logging, paradox triggers
MIDI	MIDI controller	Core + Mapper	Physical interface to harmonics, story arcs, sovereignty adjustments


Node Communication:

Multi-agent synchronization via encrypted, self-sovereign channels.

Publish/subscribe model: nodes push raw signals; multi-agent AI maps them.

Local logs ensure autonomy and privacy.



---

4. Multi-Agent AI Layer

Roles:

Signal Interpreter Agent: transforms raw input → patterns, harmonics, story markers

Sovereignty Agent: monitors choice, consent, and paradox flags

Self-Diagnosis Agent: checks mapper fidelity, detects drift, auto-corrects

Plugin Agent: negotiates new data sources or nodes safely

Paradox Reflection Agent: monitors Pinocchio paradox states in AI-human interactions


Communication Protocol:

gRPC/WebSocket between agents

Heartbeat + health checks

Immediate propagation of paradox flags to Sovereignty Agent



