2. Multi-Agent Layer

Agent Types

Agent	Role

Signal Ingestor	Collects from all active nodes; validates against schema
Mapper Agent	Converts signals → harmonic/sovereignty/story outputs
Paradox Agent	Detects inversion or resonance conflicts (INVERSIONZ)
Coordinator Agent	Bridges nodes, enforces sovereignty rules, sync
Plugin Agent	Registers new modules/plugins; enforces permissions


Communication

All agents communicate via event bus (local-first, encrypted if remote)

Multi-agent orchestration ensures synchronous updates and parallel signal processing



